.TH "WINDOW.UNLOAD_EVENT" "3JS" "November 6, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Window.unload_event \- Window: unload event
.SH SYNOPSIS
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Warning:\f[R] Developers should avoid using this event.
See \(lqUsage notes\(rq below.
.RE
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]unload\f[B]\f[R] event is fired when the document or a
child resource is being unloaded.
.PP
It is fired after:
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]beforeunload\f[R] (cancelable event)
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]pagehide\f[R]
.PP
The document is in the following state:
.IP \(bu 2
All the resources still exist (img, iframe etc.)
.IP \(bu 2
Nothing is visible anymore to the end user
.IP \(bu 2
UI interactions are ineffective (\f[CR]window.open\f[R],
\f[CR]alert\f[R], \f[CR]confirm\f[R], etc.)
.IP \(bu 2
An error won\(cqt stop the unloading workflow
.PP
Please note that the unload event also follows the document tree: parent
frame unload will happen \f[B]before\f[R] child frame \f[CR]unload\f[R]
(see example below).
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\(dqunload\(dq, (event) => { })

onunload = (event) => { }
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A generic \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EVENT HANDLER ALIASES
In addition to the \f[CR]Window\f[R] interface, the event handler
property \f[CR]onunload\f[R] is also available on the following targets:
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]HTMLBodyElement\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]HTMLFrameSetElement\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]SVGSVGElement\f[R]
.SH USAGE NOTES
Developers should avoid using this event.
.PP
Especially on mobile, the \f[CR]unload\f[R] event is not reliably fired.
For example, the \f[CR]unload\f[R] event is not fired at all in the
following scenario:
.IP "1." 3
A mobile user visits your page.
.IP "2." 3
The user then switches to a different app.
.IP "3." 3
Later, the user closes the browser from the app manager.
.PP
Also, the \f[CR]unload\f[R] event is not compatible with the \c
.UR https://web.dev/articles/bfcache
back/forward cache
.UE \c
\ (bfcache), because many pages using this event assume that the page
will not continue to exist after the event is fired.
To combat this, some browsers (such as Firefox) will not place pages in
the bfcache if they have unload listeners, and this is bad for
performance.
Others, such as Chrome, will not fire the \f[CR]unload\f[R] when a user
navigates away.
.PP
The best event to use to signal the end of a user\(cqs session is the
\f[CR]visibilitychange\f[R] event.
In browsers that don\(cqt support \f[CR]visibilitychange\f[R] the
next\-best alternative is the \f[CR]pagehide\f[R] event, which is also
not fired reliably, but which is bfcache\-compatible.
.PP
If you\(cqre specifically trying to detect page unload events, it\(cqs
best to listen for the \f[CR]pagehide\f[R] event.
.PP
See the \c
.UR https://developer.chrome.com/docs/web-platform/page-lifecycle-api#the-unload-event
Page Lifecycle API
.UE \c
\ guide for more information about the problems associated with the
\f[CR]unload\f[R] event.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
<!doctype html>
<\f[B]html\f[R] lang=\(dqen\-US\(dq>
  <\f[B]head\f[R]>
    <\f[B]meta\f[R] charset=\(dqUTF\-8\(dq />
    <\f[B]title\f[R]>Parent Frame</\f[B]title\f[R]>
    <\f[B]script\f[R]>
      window.addEventListener(\(dqbeforeunload\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
        console.log(\(dqI am the 1st one.\(dq);
      });
      window.addEventListener(\(dqunload\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
        console.log(\(dqI am the 3rd one.\(dq);
      });
    </\f[B]script\f[R]>
  </\f[B]head\f[R]>
  <\f[B]body\f[R]>
    <\f[B]iframe\f[R] src=\(dqchild\-frame.html\(dq></\f[B]iframe\f[R]>
  </\f[B]body\f[R]>
</\f[B]html\f[R]>
.EE
.PP
Below, the content of \f[CR]child\-frame.html\f[R]:
.IP
.EX
<!doctype html>
<\f[B]html\f[R] lang=\(dqen\-US\(dq>
  <\f[B]head\f[R]>
    <\f[B]meta\f[R] charset=\(dqUTF\-8\(dq />
    <\f[B]title\f[R]>Child Frame</\f[B]title\f[R]>
    <\f[B]script\f[R]>
      window.addEventListener(\(dqbeforeunload\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
        console.log(\(dqI am the 2nd one.\(dq);
      });
      window.addEventListener(\(dqunload\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
        console.log(\(dqI am the 4th and last one\&...\(dq);
      });
    </\f[B]script\f[R]>
  </\f[B]head\f[R]>
  <\f[B]body\f[R]>
    ☻
  </\f[B]body\f[R]>
</\f[B]html\f[R]>
.EE
.PP
When the parent frame is unloaded, events will be fired in the order
described by the \f[CR]console.log()\f[R] messages.
